{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3a74c094-7b58-483a-8b3d-4350ba24093c","content":"MSTest v3 **dropped support for `.testsettings` files**. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's how to translate your configuration:\n\n**Create a `.runsettings` file** (e.g., `local.runsettings`):\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>\n    <AssemblyResolution>\n      <Directory useLoadContext=\"true\" />\n    </AssemblyResolution>\n  </MSTest>\n  <RunConfiguration>\n    <TestSessionTimeout>30000</TestSessionTimeout>\n  </RunConfiguration>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n**Key mapping:**\n| `.testsettings` | `.runsettings` |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` property | `<TestSessionTimeout>` in `<RunConfiguration>` |\n| `DataCollector` in `<AgentRule>` | `<DataCollectors>` in `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` |\n| `AssemblyResolution` | `<AssemblyResolution>` under `<MSTest>` |\n\n**To use it**, either:\n- Pass `--settings local.runsettings` to `dotnet test`\n- Or add to your `.csproj`:\n  ```xml\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  ```\n\nYou can then delete `local.testsettings`. Want me to create the `.runsettings` file and update your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6ff2962b-fb8c-4c78-b79b-77ac42f30f8b","outputTokens":520,"requestId":"8433:BD22C:265BA91:2A07A1E:6A0AD928"},"id":"95cbab0d-ac6e-418e-8e3b-165fe192400c","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:17:37.835Z","parentId":"719ad49b-6551-4b82-a711-2a145